TY  - JOUR
T1  - How Much Did the Liberty Shipbuilders Forget?
AU  - Thompson, Peter
Y1  - 2007/06/01
PY  - 2007
DA  - 2007/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.1060.0678
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.1060.0678
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 908
EP  - 918
VL  - 53
IS  - 6
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - This paper produces new estimates of the rate of organizational forgetting in the well-known case study of U.S. wartime ship production. Estimates obtained using data constructed from primary sources at the National Archives yield rates of forgetting that are much smaller than previously reported, and may well be zero. The richness of the data makes it possible to control for variations in the product mix, to explore alternative formulations for the learning curve, and to investigate the relationship between organizational forgetting and labor turnover.
AB  - This paper produces new estimates of the rate of organizational forgetting in the well-known case study of U.S. wartime ship production. Estimates obtained using data constructed from primary sources at the National Archives yield rates of forgetting that are much smaller than previously reported, and may well be zero. The richness of the data makes it possible to control for variations in the product mix, to explore alternative formulations for the learning curve, and to investigate the relationship between organizational forgetting and labor turnover.
